.TH "TAKO" "1" "Jun 2026" "Tako CLI" "Tako CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
tako-config-export - Materialize remote takod state into a tako.yaml


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtako config export [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Read desired, actual, and deployment history state from a remote takod node
through SSH and takod's Unix socket, then materialize that Tako state into a
valid tako.yaml. This reads Tako-managed replicated state; it does not discover
arbitrary non-Tako containers.

.PP
Use --file/-o to write the generated YAML/JSON config to a file. The deprecated
local --output FILE form is still accepted for file paths, while --output text
and --output json select the global machine-output format for compatibility.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--environment\fP="production"
	Environment name to read from takod state

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--file\fP=""
	Write generated config to this file instead of stdout

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for export

.PP
\fB--no-validate\fP[=false]
	Skip validation of the generated config

.PP
\fB--output\fP=""
	Legacy config file path; use --file/-o. Values text/json select machine output format

.PP
\fB--password\fP=""
	SSH password for the remote takod node (not written to output)

.PP
\fB--project\fP=""
	Project name to read from takod state (required)

.PP
\fB--server\fP=""
	SSH host for the remote takod node (required)

.PP
\fB--server-name\fP=""
	Remote target node/server key to attach connection details to when exporting multi-node state (defaults to a sanitized form of --server)

.PP
\fB--socket\fP=""
	Remote takod Unix socket path

.PP
\fB--ssh-key\fP="~/.ssh/id_rsa"
	SSH private key for the remote takod node

.PP
\fB--ssh-port\fP=22
	SSH port for the remote takod node

.PP
\fB--user\fP=""
	SSH user for the remote takod node (defaults to current user)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is ./tako.yaml or ./tako.json)

.PP
\fB-e\fP, \fB--env\fP=""
	environment to deploy (default: production or only environment)

.PP
\fB--events\fP=""
	stream progress events to stdout: ndjson (human output moves to stderr)

.PP
\fB--host-key-mode\fP=""
	SSH host key verification mode: tofu, strict, ask (default: tofu)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	verbose output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBtako-config(1)\fP
